class digitinterface.digitinterface.BasicClient(url, protocols=None, extensions=None, heartbeat_freq=None, ssl_options=None, headers=None, exclude_headers=None)[source]

Bases: WebSocketClient

Websocket Client Class

Parameters

  • ip (string) – Websocket URI. For simulation, it is “ws://127.0.0.1:8080” and for the physical robot, it is “ws://10.10.1.1:8080”

  • protocols (List{string}) – It is always [“json-v1-agility”]

Returns

A web socket object with which you can send and receive JSON messages to digit as well as open or close the web socket connection

Return type

get_wrist_pose(armname, reference_frame='base')[source]

Returns the pose rpyxyz of the wrist of Digit

Parameters

  • armname (string) – “left” or “right”

  • reference_frame (string) – Frame of reference of the wrist pose. The default is “base” which is the pelvis of Digit.

Returns

The pose of the wrist in a python List formatted as [roll pitch yaw x y z]

Return type

List{Float64}

move_both_arms_sequentially_to_pose(pose, armname, prevarmname, prevarmpose, duration=2.0)[source]

Maintains the pose of one wrist as the other wrist moves to a specified pose

Parameters

  • pose (List{float}) – The desired pose of the target wrist in a python List formatted as [roll pitch yaw x y z]

  • armname (string) – “left” or “right”. The name of the target wrist

  • prevarmname (string) – “left” or “right”. The name of the other arm

  • prevarmpose (List{float}) – The pose at which to maintain the other arm in a python List formatted as [roll pitch yaw x y z]

  • duration (float) – The desired duration of the entire motion in seconds.

move_both_wrists_to_pose(lpose, rpose, duration=2.0)[source]

Moves both wrists concurrently to the specified poses

Parameters

  • lpose (List{float}) – The desired pose of the left wrist in a python List formatted as [roll pitch yaw x y z]

  • rpose (List{float}) – The desired pose of the right wrist in a python List formatted as [roll pitch yaw x y z]

  • duration (float) – The desired duration of the entire motion in seconds.
